From: Trung Lê <8@tle.id.au>
Subject: doc: route help-family bitmap paths through CDE_DATA_TOP

The .hf (help family) files at the top of $(CDE_DATA_TOP)/appconfig/help/<LANG>/
have an absolute *.bitmap: pointer to the cdelogo.pm graphic dthelpview shows
beside the "Common Desktop Environment" and "Overview and Basic Desktop Skills"
section headers in the Help Manager's main window.

The 12 .hf.in templates (Desktop.hf.in + DesktopIntro.hf.in across 6 locales)
substitute the path with @prefix@:

    *.bitmap:       @prefix@/appconfig/help/en_US.UTF-8/graphics/cdelogo.pm

With --prefix=/usr (FHS) this expands to /usr/appconfig/help/.../cdelogo.pm,
which does not exist; the install actually puts the graphic at
$(CDE_DATA_TOP)/appconfig/help/.../cdelogo.pm (i.e. /usr/share/cde/appconfig/
help/.../ on Fedora). dthelpview can't resolve the bitmap and renders a
"Missing Graphics" placeholder.

Replace @prefix@ with @CDE_DATA_TOP@ so the path tracks --with-cde-data-dir
the same way every other data-tree path does after Patch0008.

diff --git a/doc/de_DE.UTF-8/help/common/Desktop.hf.in b/doc/de_DE.UTF-8/help/common/Desktop.hf.in
index e374c251f..bf73ff06f 100644
--- a/doc/de_DE.UTF-8/help/common/Desktop.hf.in
+++ b/doc/de_DE.UTF-8/help/common/Desktop.hf.in
@@ -16,7 +16,7 @@
 
 *.charSet:      UTF-8
 *.title:        Common Desktop Environment
-*.bitmap:       @prefix@/appconfig/help/de_DE.UTF-8/graphics/cdelogo.pm
+*.bitmap:       @CDE_DATA_TOP@/appconfig/help/de_DE.UTF-8/graphics/cdelogo.pm
 *.abstract:     Überblick und Grundkenntnisse für das Desktop \
  * Hilfe für Hilfe \
  * Anwendungsmanager \
